---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Astro + Tailwind + TypeScript" description="Learn more about the Astro + Tailwind + TypeScript template">
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-8 px-6 sm:px-8 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About</h1>
    
    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p class="mb-4">
        This is a minimal starter template built with Astro, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript. 
        It provides a solid foundation for building modern, fast, and type-safe websites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Why This Stack?</h2>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Astro</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Astro is a modern web framework that allows you to build faster websites with less client-side JavaScript.
        It features an "Islands Architecture" that lets you ship only the JavaScript that's needed.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Tailwind CSS</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework that enables rapid UI development.
        It provides a set of utility classes that help you build custom designs without ever leaving your HTML.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">TypeScript</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        TypeScript adds static type definitions to JavaScript, improving developer experience through
        better tooling, error checking, and code completion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout> 